E. COLI VTEC - USA (10): (NORTH CAROLINA), FAIR LINK, MORE CASES
****************************************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 3 Nov 2011
Source: WNCT [edited]
http://www2.wnct.com/news/2011/oct/27/18/nine-sickened-nc-e-coli-ar-1545463/


The _E. coli_ outbreak across our state continues to grow this
afternoon [3 Nov 2011], and health officials still haven't pinpointed
the source.

State health officials are investigating 30 confirmed or suspected
cases, all linked to the State Fair. That's 3 more than we reported on
Tue 1 Nov 2011. Six people are still in the hospital this afternoon [3
Nov 2011], 5 of them children.

[Byline: Jonathan Rodriguez]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Since ProMED last reported on this cluster of enterohemorrhagic _E.
coli_, there have been 6 more cases added to the total, all with links
to the recent State Fair in Raleigh. So far, no definitive vehicle has
been elucidated. - Mod.LL]
